The paper deals with the problem of learning the parameters of a Gaussian mixture model, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a differentially private algorithm, which involves techniques from cryptography and information theory, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves analyzing the sample complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
